databasepackage

Class MyTable

  • java.lang.Object
    • databasepackage.MyTable

  • public class MyTable
extends Object
    The MyTable class is a relational database toolkit intended for light weight use cases such as prototype or personal projects, where a full DBMS may be unnecessary. This implementation is fully built using java making it highly portable.
    Author:
    Saud Fatayerji

      • getFilterOp

        public FilterOp getFilterOp(String[] colTitles,
                            HashSet<String>[] values)
        Gets a new FilterOp. The FilterOp searches for rows where each specified column contains a value found in the respective set of values.
        Parameters:
        colTitles - The titles of the columns to check.
        values - The values to check for. Each set of the values array corresponds to the title in the same position in the colTitles array.
        Returns:
        The new new FilterOp. The FilterOp.getResult() method of the returned value returns a MyTable object. The results of the returned operation must be calculated using the runOp() method.

      • getFilterOp

        public FilterOp getFilterOp(String colTitle,

      • getCatColumnsOp

        public CatColumnsOp getCatColumnsOp(String newTableName,
                                    String newColTitle,
                                    String separator,
                                    String... colsToJoin)
        Gets a new CatColumnsOp. Concatenates the values of multiple columns. The new column is added to the end of a new table.
        Parameters:
        newTableName - The name for the new table.
        newColTitle - The title of the column that will be created.
        separator - The separator used when concatenating the values in the columns.
        colsToJoin - The titles of the columns to join. The order provided here will match the order that the values are joined in. These will be removed from the resulting table.
        Returns:
        The new new CatColumnsOp. The CatColumnsOp.getResult() method of the returned value returns a MyTable object. The results of the returned operation must be calculated using the runOp() method.

      • getInsertColsOp

        public InsertColsOp getInsertColsOp(String newTableName,
                                    int position,
                                    String newColTitle,
                                    String defaultValue)
        Inserts a new column into specified position of a new table. The column will be filled with the specified default value.
        Parameters:
        newTableName - The name for the new table.
        newColTitle - The title of the column that will be created.
        position - The index of the column to insert at. Similar to ArrayList.add(int index, E element).
        defaultValue - The value that the column will be filled with.
        Returns:
        The new new InsertColsOp. The InsertColsOp.getResult() method of the returned value returns a MyTable object. The results of the returned operation must be calculated using the runOp() method.

        public Object[] runOps(boolean parse,
                       int threadCount,
                       TableOperationInterface... ops)
        Runs all provided ops on each of the rows in the table. Can be multi-threaded.
        Parameters:
        parse - If the rows should be parsed before being passed to the TableOperationInterface.runOp() methods. Note: refer to the parseRow() method for more information on parsing.
        threadCount - The number of threads to use for this operation. Set this to -1 to set the number automatically.
        ops - The operations to run on the provided rows.
        Returns:
        An array of all the results from the given ops as returned by the TableOperationInterface.getOpsArrResults() method.

      • getParsedRow

        public String[] getParsedRow(String recordId)
        CAUTION: This function is susceptible to code injection!!
        Parses the functions found in the given row.
        A function begins with an '=' and can contain any operations supported in the JavaScript language. Values from other cells in the same row can be accessed by using the pattern 'COLUMN_TITLE' which will be replaced with the actual value before parsing.
        Parameters:
        recordId - The primary key of the row to parse.
        Returns:
        The parsed row.
        Throws:
        RuntimeException - If the size of the row added is not equal to the number of columns.
